"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-gabby-thomas-healthcare-career-olympic-gold-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Of course Jennifer Randall is thrilled that her daughter, Gabby Thomas, will head to Paris later this month to compete in her second Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 26, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"score\": 0.9999994255787727, \"rank\": 5.74017724574379e-07, \"text\": \"Randall\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\"}, {\"begin\": 58, \"end\": 70, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999999417923, \"rank\": 5.823537400570362e-11, \"text\": \"Gabby Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 85, \"end\": 90, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9969016885049966, \"rank\": 0.003107940863609571, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Young Gabby was always faster than her peers; her grade school soccer team strategy was to boot the ball over everyone else\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s head and let Gabby chase it down.\", \"from\": 148, \"to\": 309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Randall was the one who told her she could do this, who when Gabby was 11 or 12 proclaimed that she would be an Olympic runner.\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"score\": 0.9999994255787727, \"rank\": 5.74017724574379e-07, \"text\": \"Randall\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cShe rolled her eyes at me and sashayed out of the room,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Randall says.\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"score\": 0.9999994255787727, \"rank\": 5.74017724574379e-07, \"text\": \"Randall\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But a dozen years later, there Thomas was,earning a bronze medal in Tokyoin the 200 meters, and a silver in the 4x100, while Randall watched, delighted.\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 545, \"end\": 551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"score\": 0.9999994255787727, \"rank\": 5.74017724574379e-07, \"text\": \"Randall\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has her Paris itinerary all planned.\\u00c2  After Paris, Thomas hopes to compete in Los Angeles in 2028, and that's all fine with her mom.\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 679, \"end\": 684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9969016885049966, \"rank\": 0.003107940863609571, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9969016885049966, \"rank\": 0.003107940863609571, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 723, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0958299188263088e-23, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Great, even.\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 817, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But then that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s enough of that.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI mean, come on!\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Randall laments.\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cShe has to get a Ph.D.\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t even understand why she argues with me about this.\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been obvious from the beginning.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1020, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll come to realize that I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m absolutely right.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve been right about all things, by the way.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The 27-year-old Thomas, a bit of her preteen self peeking through, groans and laughs.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1156, \"end\": 1162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThat\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s her biggest goal in life right now,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Randall, a professor of education at Michigan, has spent nearly three decades instilling in Thomas and her twin brother, Andrew, an artist, that they can do and be anything they want to be.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1325, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Michigan\", \"score\": 0.9999999998753992, \"rank\": 1.2291829906740652e-10, \"text\": \"Michigan\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Michigan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Michigan\"}, {\"begin\": 1380, \"end\": 1386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What Gabby Thomas wants to be is the president of a hospital.\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1483, \"end\": 1495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999999417923, \"rank\": 5.823537400570362e-11, \"text\": \"Gabby Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But first she has to finish getting what her mother callslife experience: that is, trying to win Olympic gold.\\u00c2  These days, when Thomas thinks about beinggood enough, she is generally referring to the weights she lifts, to the rest she gets, to the times she runs.\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1670, \"end\": 1676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And she tends to pass every test she gives herself: In 2023, she took silver at the world championships in the 200 meters and gold in the 4x100.\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In June, she won the Olympic trials in the 200 meters in 21.81 seconds, nearly a tenth of a second ahead of second place.\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 2072, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But for a long time, she asked that question about herself as a person.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think that I have consistently been in uncomfortable situations where I had to rise to the occasion or rise to the environment that I was in,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe moved around quite a bit when I was younger, so I was kind of forced to be uncomfortable for a little bit and then make it work.\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Making new friends, developing new relationships, proving that I belonged in that space.\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2530, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It also comes with being a young Black girl, being in very predominantly white environments, and feeling like I needed to prove that I belonged in those environments and I wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t that different, and that I was smart enough, that I was pretty enough, that I was good enough.\\\"\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas attended The Williston Northampton School, a private boarding high school in Easthampton, Mass., before enrolling at Harvard.\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2809, \"end\": 2815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 2829, \"end\": 2857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Williston_Northampton_School\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Williston Northampton School\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Williston_Northampton_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Williston_Northampton_School\"}, {\"begin\": 2893, \"end\": 2904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shobdon\", \"score\": 0.9999999974143066, \"rank\": 2.220101765091114e-09, \"text\": \"Easthampton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shobdon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shobdon\"}, {\"begin\": 2906, \"end\": 2910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9258762632696423, \"rank\": 0.08005543064322819, \"text\": \"Mass\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_in_the_Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 2933, \"end\": 2940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"score\": 0.9977699281003465, \"rank\": 0.0022350543514604573, \"text\": \"Harvard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She says she felt like she had to prove she belonged in both environments.\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 3016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had to tell myself and really believe in my heart that I did belong,\\\" she says.\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3099, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I decided to study neurobiology, I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m in classes with people who\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094I can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t even tell you how insanely smart and ingenious those people are, but I just sat in those classes and contributed and asked questions, and I had to believe that I wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t asking stupid questions, or else I wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t going to make it.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2  Early her freshman year, she found herself failing LS1B, introduction to internal life sciences.\", \"from\": 3100, \"to\": 3518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was actually failing,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 3519, \"to\": 3558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cNot like that cute \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098failing,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 where people are like, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098Haha!\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 Like, I was gonna drop the class.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d If she did, she would either need to repeat the semester or choose a major other than neurobiology.\", \"from\": 3559, \"to\": 3767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the professor convinced her she could do it and worked with her to make a plan.\", \"from\": 3768, \"to\": 3851, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She graduated on time with that degree.\\u00c2  At times she felt the same way about track, which she initially ran because she was good at it and it was fun.\", \"from\": 3852, \"to\": 4004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But by the summer after her sophomore year at Harvard, she was about ready to be done with it.\", \"from\": 4005, \"to\": 4099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4051, \"end\": 4058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"score\": 0.9977699281003465, \"rank\": 0.0022350543514604573, \"text\": \"Harvard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She wanted to focus more on studying global health.\", \"from\": 4100, \"to\": 4151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the more she learned about other people\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s lives, the easier hers seemed.\", \"from\": 4152, \"to\": 4230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(She also used her mother\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s experience as a yardstick: Randall grew up as one of nine children in a two-bedroom house, the electricity out most days, and put herself through school with waitressing and teaching jobs, before raising Gabby and Andrew as a single mom.\", \"from\": 4231, \"to\": 4498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4288, \"end\": 4295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"score\": 0.9999994255787727, \"rank\": 5.74017724574379e-07, \"text\": \"Randall\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI remember thinking, if she could do that, then whatever I was doing was not hard,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Thomas says.)\", \"from\": 4499, \"to\": 4601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4588, \"end\": 4594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She stuck with track, and\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094after agreeing with Randall that she would choose an elite running program near a school with an elite public health master\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s program\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094moved to Austin, Texas.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was not even close to being an Olympian myself,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBut I forced myself to go train with them, and I forced myself to get my butt kicked in practice every day for two years, so that when the time came, I was ready to make the Olympic team.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  This is the attitude her mother always hoped to instill in her.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis is what I hope,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Randall.\", \"from\": 4602, \"to\": 5161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4650, \"end\": 4657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"score\": 0.9999994255787727, \"rank\": 5.74017724574379e-07, \"text\": \"Randall\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\"}, {\"begin\": 4777, \"end\": 4783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\", \"score\": 0.9992352613263247, \"rank\": 0.0007630461462799008, \"text\": \"Austin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\"}, {\"begin\": 4830, \"end\": 4838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999995652615, \"rank\": 4.350889357310454e-10, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 5153, \"end\": 5160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"score\": 0.9999994255787727, \"rank\": 5.74017724574379e-07, \"text\": \"Randall\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou know, we always try to work out our stuff on our kids.\", \"from\": 5162, \"to\": 5223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I absolutely feel that way, and I have always felt that way, that I wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t good enough to be in different types of spaces.\", \"from\": 5224, \"to\": 5352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I think many of the spaces that Gabby walks into are remarkably elite spaces.\", \"from\": 5353, \"to\": 5434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I think many Black women suffer with this term that I hate, but it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s real: imposter syndrome.\", \"from\": 5435, \"to\": 5534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I think what I wanted for Gabby was to not have that, to know that she was always smart, to know that she was always talented and gorgeous and all of these things.\", \"from\": 5535, \"to\": 5702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the world tells her differently all the time, right?\", \"from\": 5703, \"to\": 5759, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The world especially tells Black women all the time that this space does not belong to you.\", \"from\": 5760, \"to\": 5851, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And her mom couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t undo the world.\", \"from\": 5852, \"to\": 5890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But what\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s great about Gabby is that she walks into the spaces anyway, and that I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m proud of.\", \"from\": 5891, \"to\": 5988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean, at least I taught her to do that: Even when you feel like you don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t belong there, show up and show out.\", \"from\": 5989, \"to\": 6102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s what she does, every single time.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Says Thomas, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt is really hard.\", \"from\": 6103, \"to\": 6188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6159, \"end\": 6165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And there are definitely days where you think you don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t want to do it.\", \"from\": 6189, \"to\": 6261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are so many days where I wanted to quit, but you just do it.\", \"from\": 6262, \"to\": 6328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each day, you make a decision that you belong there.\", \"from\": 6329, \"to\": 6381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And eventually you do.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Her challenge now is that everyone else knows she belongs, too.\", \"from\": 6382, \"to\": 6472, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, she raced at Olympic Trials not expecting to make the team.\", \"from\": 6473, \"to\": 6541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She ran a 21.61 200-meter race, then the third-fastest time ever recorded.\", \"from\": 6542, \"to\": 6616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI am still in shock,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said afterward.\", \"from\": 6617, \"to\": 6664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI cannot believe I put up that time.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d) In Tokyo, she wandered joyfully around the Olympic Village, just trying to soak it all in.\", \"from\": 6665, \"to\": 6799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6712, \"end\": 6717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9993782748451164, \"rank\": 0.0006221114512433989, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She came home with those two medals.\", \"from\": 6800, \"to\": 6836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Randall gave her about 30 seconds to celebrate before mentioning her fall semester at the University of Texas.)\", \"from\": 6837, \"to\": 6949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6838, \"end\": 6845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"score\": 0.9999994255787727, \"rank\": 5.74017724574379e-07, \"text\": \"Randall\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, Thomas felt set to improve upon her Tokyo performance at the world championships, but she sustained a Grade 2 strain of her right hamstring in a training run two weeks before trials.\", \"from\": 6951, \"to\": 7142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6960, \"end\": 6966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 6996, \"end\": 7001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9993782748451164, \"rank\": 0.0006221114512433989, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She studied peer-reviewed literature and decided that daily three-hour sessions in a hyperbaric chamber would provide her best chance of healing in time.\", \"from\": 7143, \"to\": 7296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She recovered enough to make the finals at trials, but she finished eighth and did not qualify for worlds.\", \"from\": 7297, \"to\": 7403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(She was named to the team as a possibility on the relay squad, but the coaches did not use her.)\", \"from\": 7404, \"to\": 7501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was crushed.\", \"from\": 7502, \"to\": 7518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, she believes that the time off helped her focus on the journey, which is perspective she needs now that she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not an underdog anymore.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cGoing into Tokyo, no one really believed in me, which made it a little bit easier,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 7519, \"to\": 7763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7679, \"end\": 7684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9993782748451164, \"rank\": 0.0006221114512433989, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt was really just about my journey and having fun.\", \"from\": 7764, \"to\": 7818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s all upside.\", \"from\": 7819, \"to\": 7837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And now the gold is really mine to lose, and every time I step on the track, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s my race to lose.\", \"from\": 7838, \"to\": 7938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So you definitely have to have another reason for competing other than just winning.\", \"from\": 7939, \"to\": 8023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winning cannot be your end all, be all to sport.\", \"from\": 8024, \"to\": 8072, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It cannot be your reason to exist or reason to be.\", \"from\": 8073, \"to\": 8123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So for me, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s about just being my best self.\", \"from\": 8124, \"to\": 8172, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s about showcasing what you can do.\", \"from\": 8173, \"to\": 8213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I know that there are a lot of people watching, especially the younger generation, and other girls who are watching us compete the same way that I did growing up.\", \"from\": 8214, \"to\": 8380, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And so it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s: How can I be a great role model for them?\", \"from\": 8381, \"to\": 8437, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How can I be an example for them?\", \"from\": 8438, \"to\": 8471, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What do I want to leave the sport?\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The answer extends far beyond track.\", \"from\": 8472, \"to\": 8547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She got her master\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in public health and epidemiology from Texas, where she wrote her thesis on racial health disparities as an outcome of sleep issues.\", \"from\": 8548, \"to\": 8703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8610, \"end\": 8615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Texas_at_Austin\", \"score\": 0.9999999923074938, \"rank\": 7.458159965603408e-09, \"text\": \"Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Texas_at_Austin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Texas_at_Austin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She spends 10 hours a week volunteering at an Austin health clinic, running an intervention program for patients with hypertension.\", \"from\": 8704, \"to\": 8835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8750, \"end\": 8756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\", \"score\": 0.9992352613263247, \"rank\": 0.0007630461462799008, \"text\": \"Austin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(She convinced New Balance, one of her sponsors, to donate running shoes for them all.\", \"from\": 8836, \"to\": 8922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8851, \"end\": 8862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Balance\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Balance\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Balance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Balance\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSneakers are really expensive!\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt really made their day.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d) She has365,000 Instagram followers, but Randall loves that \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cshe has committed her life to working for people who will never, ever, ever know her name,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 8923, \"to\": 9167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9042, \"end\": 9049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"score\": 0.9999994255787727, \"rank\": 5.74017724574379e-07, \"text\": \"Randall\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randall_Amplifiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So Thomas will run the 200 meters and likely the 4x100 meters in Paris, then she will return to Austin, where she will continue on both tracks simultaneously.\", \"from\": 9169, \"to\": 9327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9172, \"end\": 9178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9139465996787446, \"rank\": 0.07787217291018682, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 9234, \"end\": 9239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9969016885049966, \"rank\": 0.003107940863609571, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 9265, \"end\": 9271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\", \"score\": 0.9992352613263247, \"rank\": 0.0007630461462799008, \"text\": \"Austin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stone_Cold_Steve_Austin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve forced myself to do it for so long now that I do think that if I were to ever put myself in a situation where I wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t uncomfortable, I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d be uncomfortable with that,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 9329, \"to\": 9521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d feel like I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m not growing.\", \"from\": 9522, \"to\": 9559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I would get bored.\", \"from\": 9560, \"to\": 9578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m always kind of looking for that next challenge.\", \"from\": 9579, \"to\": 9635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Right now, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s striving and chasing after a gold medal, and we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll see what it will be after that.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2  Her mom has a suggestion.\", \"from\": 9636, \"to\": 9769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 9771, \"to\": 9797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Stephanie Apstein is a senior writer covering baseball and Olympic sports for Sports Illustrated, where she started as an intern in 2011 and has since covered a dozen World Series and three Olympics.\", \"from\": 9798, \"to\": 10061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9862, \"end\": 9871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.628443665936389e-14, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\"}, {\"begin\": 9940, \"end\": 9958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.912250275165024e-33, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has twice won top honors from the Associated Press Sports Editors, and her work has been included in the Best American Sports Writing book series.\", \"from\": 10062, \"to\": 10212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10100, \"end\": 10116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999954216037, \"rank\": 4.5781804048991825e-09, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 10171, \"end\": 10199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Best American Sports Writing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She graduated from Trinity College with a bachelor\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in French and Italian, and has a master\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in journalism from Columbia University.\", \"from\": 10213, \"to\": 10351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10232, \"end\": 10247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5159353931056297e-13, \"text\": \"Trinity College\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_University\"}, {\"begin\": 10331, \"end\": 10350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbia_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6170384915781153e-13, \"text\": \"Columbia University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbia_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbia_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC.\", \"from\": 10353, \"to\": 10430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 10431, \"to\": 10453, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only.\", \"from\": 10454, \"to\": 10530, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands.\", \"from\": 10531, \"to\": 10725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10658, \"end\": 10676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.912250275165024e-33, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit.\", \"from\": 10726, \"to\": 10814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 10815, \"to\": 10947, \"entities\": []}]}"